Ad Text:
About the client
Our client is a multi national fertility business and leader in its field. 
 
About the role
A detail-oriented and analytical Commercial Analyst is requitred to support technology initiatives. In this role, you will deliver commercial, analytical, and vendor management support to the Tech services function, and support other improvement initiatives.

What's Required
▪ Bachelor’s degree in business, Information Technology, or a related field; Master’s degree preferred.
▪ Demonstrated experience in technology analysis, business analysis, or strategy development.
▪ Demonstrated interpersonal and negotiation skills in dealing with key stakeholders including senior management, consultants, contractors, and committees.
▪ Strong analytical skills with proficiency in data analysis tools and methodologies.
▪ Excellent verbal and written communication skills, including the ability to collaborate with cross-portfolio teams at different levels across organisations to deliver concise, authoritative, high quality written material.
▪ Strong problem-solving abilities and attention to detail.
▪ Proficient in Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, and other analytical tools.
▪ Financial management knowledge to monitor and manage technology services expenditure (including software licences, maintenance, and other recurring expenditure).

What's on Offer
Flexible working
The opportunity for career progression

About Us    

At Development Victoria, we’re passionate about making Victoria a great place to be. We create vibrant places across our state, through diverse and strategic property development and urban renewal projects.    

As the Victorian Government’s development arm, we revitalise iconic public buildings, create important community, creative and sporting facilities and repurpose public land, for all Victorians. We also build great homes and communities where people and businesses can thrive, catering for different budgets, lifestyles, and people - designed to be sustainable and affordable.    




Your New Role

As our Manager, People Data and Systems, you’ll lead the implementation and ongoing optimisation of our organisation‑wide HRIS and build DV’s capability in people data, reporting and analytics. You will be the owner of people data and be responsible for the overall integrity and functionality of our system. You will partner across the business to deliver clear, actionable insights that support decision‑making, workforce planning and organisational performance.

This role is a great opportunity to shape our people technology environment and uplift data literacy across the People & Culture function.

Core Accountabilities: 

HR Systems

Lead the successful delivery of DV’s new HRIS, ensuring it meets business and user needs.
Provide training, guidance and support to help teams use the system effectively.
Own the roadmap for people systems and identify opportunities to improve processes and technology.
Manage relationships with HR system vendors, implementation partners and IT.
Maintain strong governance, including user access, data integrity and change control.
Streamline and automate P&C processes and reporting wherever possible.

Data, Analytics and Insights

Deliver accurate and timely people analytics and reporting for leaders.
Build capability in advanced analytics, dashboards and visualisation tools.
Act as custodian of people data, ensuring accuracy, security and compliance.
Translate data into meaningful insights that shape workforce planning and business decisions.
Support key people processes such as remuneration reviews and other data‑dependent activities.
Conduct ad‑hoc analysis to respond to business needs.
Develop and maintain regular reports and dashboards for various audiences such as executive, board and external bodies.
Grow data literacy and awareness within the P&C team.



About You

You will be collaborative and solutions focused, bringing strong experience in HR systems, people data and analytics. You enjoy solving problems, improving processes and helping people use technology with confidence. You build strong relationships, communicate clearly and bring a thoughtful, evidence-based approach to your work. You will have had experience and/or exposure to generalist HR roles and have worked directly with Payroll and People Operations roles.

You will also bring:

Experience implementing and managing an HRIS
A solid understanding of HR processes and data models
Strong data analysis and reporting skills
Strong critical thinking
Experience with dashboarding or analytics tools (e.g. Power BI, Tableau)
Knowledge of data governance, privacy and security
Strong stakeholder engagement and the ability to influence leaders
High attention to detail and a process‑driven mindset
Relevant qualifications in HR, Business, Data Analytics or similar

Employee Benefits

We drive strong collaboration and support our teams to work virtually and flexibly.
Professional development opportunities available including;

Study support
Leadership Development
Opportunity to participate in cross functional working groups that drive diversity and inclusion and sustainability initiatives.
Novated leasing
Purchase leave
Paid parental leave
Technology salary sacrifice
Employee referral bonuses
Health & Wellbeing initiatives such as EAP and mental health and wellbeing leave
Access to group life & group salary continuance insurance
Modern onsite facilities

Application Process

Please apply via our careers page linked to this advertisement, applications will not be accepted via email.
Advert may close prior to the closure date if a high volume of applications is received so we encourage you to apply as soon as possible.
Please note: The preferred candidate will be required to complete a national police record check prior to an offer of employment being made.
At Development Victoria, we work flexibly and value diversity, and we invite you to talk to us about any preferences or adjustments you may value or require to either our recruitment process or the role itself. If you identify as a person with disability, please let us know how we can provide additional support to your application


Application Deadline:
Please submit your application by 8 February 2026. Applications received after this date may not be considered.


We respectfully request no agency approaches. We will not be responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes being sent to anyone here in our business.

Job Title: ServiceNow Business Solution Consultant I Business Analyst
Ad Text:
Who we are:
We’re redefining ServiceNow consulting—fusing elite expertise with startup agility to deliver transformative solutions that outsmart traditional Big-4 firms. We are one of the fastest growing software consulting firms and strongest ServiceNow Pure-play Partner across Australia and New Zealand.   

Our growth has been driven by a relentless focus on innovation, our own product development, and an outstanding customer-first culture – reflected in our customer satisfaction ratings consistently above 4.9/5. We are also on the radar of major industry analysts and global enterprise customers alike.   

At our core, we believe in empowering people to thrive and grow, whether that’s our clients or our team. 

Why You’ll Love Working Here

- Growth opportunities across Australia and New Zealand

- Flat structure, fast growth, high ownership culture

- Creative freedom to lead and implement your ideas

- Direct impact on growth, brand visibility and client experience

Please visit http://sysintegra.com.au to find out more about us. 

The Opportunity 

At Sysintegra we are looking for a Business Analyst/Solutions Consultant to be based on-site at our client in Sydney. This can be a contract or alternatively a more permanent role for the right candidate.  You will be responsible for overall design, mapping of client business requirements to systems/technical requirements. The role is required to work with clients to assess current state processes and tools, identify ServiceNow platform solution options, define ServiceNow solution requirements, determine and define integration requirements, and develop overall architecture and implementation plans. 

 
Your Key Responsibilities Will Include 

- Workshop, analyse and document business requirements related to ServiceNow integrations 

- Designing high volume, data intensive integrations 

- Translating requirements into functional specifications 

- Building integrations to big data platforms 

- Maintaining strong communication across stakeholders within the business 


Required Skills and Experience 

- Minimum of 5 years' experience as a ServiceNow Solution Consultant / Functional / Technical Business Analyst 

- Certification in ServiceNow CSA or ITIL v4 (highly regarded). 

- Strong skills in ServiceNow platform configuration and integration. 

- Knowledge of ServiceNow Integration Hub  

- Experience with designing custom integration hub 'Spokes'  

- Exposure to Workflow Data Fabric will be a strong plus as well 

- Experience with building integrations to Data Lake/Data Warehousing platforms like Google BigQuery/DataBricks would be advantageous 

- Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement capabilities

Job Title: Technical Project Manager & Systems Lead Data Analyst
Salary: $1,300 - $1,456 day inclusive of super or plus GST
Ad Text:
Our client is a high profile NSW government department that is dedicated to growing primary industries and supporting regional economic development

Role description:

The Technical Project Manager & Systems Lead Data Analyst will lead a Corporate Workforce Reporting and Automation Project (the People Dashboard Project) on the department's corporate reporting platform, Calumo / MyOutcomes, which includes integration of workforce and Human Resource data from various sources (including SAP)

This involves working with users to formulate system requirements, develop system plans and documentation, review and evaluate existing systems and design and modify systems to meet users' business needs

Responsibilities:

Partner with the workforce data team, Calumo/My Outcomes platform developers, the People team and other stakeholders across the department to understand the business needs and use cases for the development of new reports, workforce dashboard and associated visualisations.
Deliver technical project elements and ensure project deliverables are completed on time and within agreed scope.
Developing, troubleshooting and managing report logic and data accuracy.
Development of technical specifications for documentation, modelling and visualisations for development in Calumo/MyOutcomes
Working with developers to translate specifications for the development of reports
Data analysis and user acceptance testing of new reports/dashboard and document results
Diagnosing data issues and fine tuning data logic
Providing technical content to interpretation guides including caveats, limitations, inclusions / exclusions to build MyOutcomes capability and inform the development of user guides and training materials.
Ensure that business and technology risks are appropriately identified, managed and reported.
Coordination and management of deliverables within the project plan
Skills and Experience:

High level skills in workforce data and business analytics are required
Demonstrated project management experience.
System technical capability and high level skills in data analytics
Demonstrated capability to engage effectively, collaborate with and work with project partners and stakeholders
Ability to navigate disparate source data to gather required metrics for analysis and input into new reports / visualisations  
Adept at solving complex data and technical issues
Good at managing time and conflicting deliverables and ensuring that data analysis is accurate, consistent and timely
Experience in stakeholder engagement and management of technical project elements
Experience in developing technical specifications, modelling and visualisations; data analysis and testing or reported data
Consultant: Colin Massey

Keywords: Project Manager, Technical Project Manager, data, workforce data, Data Analyst, data analysis, systems analysis, data analytics, MyOutcomes, Calumo, technical specifications, modelling, visualisations, NSW government, SAP, Human Resource data, SAP, Lead Data Analyst
